reviewText: Great B noir showing the Original Portland, not the "new Portland" that Portlandia has tried to create and new residents have tried to emulate. The beauty of the original skyline, the criminal underbelly, the scenery that was not obscured by all the new construction going up now.
From what my dad told me about the movie, I thought it might be a little grittier and a little more controversial. Even for the 50's it wasn't all that disturbing. Maybe I'm just jaded.
